Incredibly, the duo were  told to report to the club on Monday and informed of their fate by interim academy director Matt Hale.

Williams,
 regarded by the academy players and their parents as one of the best 
coaches in the country at that level, was told he didn’t spend enough 
time with the players.

Dodd was informed that he was being sacked because his relationship with Hunter was not healthy.

